description:
Collectively designed standard coding protocol for the classification of Cultural Ecosystem Services (CES) through Social Media (SM) data. It includes the following files and a video tutorial to facilitate its implementation by other researchers: 
-&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Protocol.doc: a document with the general instructions on the procedure for coding; 
-&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Annex 1. CES coding.xlsx: an excel with detailed explanations and examples for each CES (one per sheet) and a last sheet, named &ldquo;coding&rdquo;, for performing the assessment; 
-&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Annex 2. Additional info.doc: to provide other coders with the details needed for performing an informed assessment; 
-&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Annex 3. Mcc.r: R code to run the Matthews Correlation Coefficient and calculate the inter- coders&rsquo; agreement; 
-&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Annex 4. Self-evaluation of the ICA.doc: to compare assessments performed by different coders and compile a site-specific annotations to the protocol. 

 - video tutorial to guide the use of the protocol.

